did.abstract: Dr. Donald Gordon was an art historian and faculty member at the University of Pittsburgh from 1969 until his death in 1984. This collection contains research conducted by Dr. Gordon throughout the world pertaining to the Expressionist Movement, particularly the paintings of Ernst Kirchner, and early twentieth century Modern Art.

bioghist.head: Biography
bioghist.p: Donald Gordon was born in New York City in 1931. He attended Havard University for his bachellor's, master's, and doctoral degrees, the latter of which he earned in 1960. In the same year, he was hired as an associate professor of fine arts at Dickinson College. In 1969, Dr. Gordon came to the University of Pittsburgh as a professor of fine arts. He served as the chair of Pitt's Fine Arts department from 1969 to 1973.

Dr. Gordon was the author of three books: Ernst Ludwig Kirchner (1968), Modern Art Exhibitions 1900-1916: Selected Catalogue Documentation (1974), and Expressionism: Art and Idea (1984). He received several professionial awards and fellowships, including honors from the American Council of Learned Societies (1973-1974) and The Alexander Humboldt Foundation Fellowship from the Central Institute for Art History in Munich (1967-1968). In addition, he served on the Board of Directors for the Society for the Arts, Religion, and Contemporary Culture from 1974 until his death in 1984. He died of cancer at the age of 52 on April 10, 1984, at Montefiore Hospital in Pittsburgh.

acqinfo.head: Acquisition Information
acqinfo.p: Gift of the Fine Arts Department in 1997.

Researchers are therefore advised to follow the regulations set forth in the U.S. Copyright Code when publishing, quoting, or reproducing material from this collection without the consent of the creator/author or that go beyond what is allowed by fair use.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content Notes
scopecontent.p: This collection contains research and drafts of several of Dr. Donald Gordon's books and articles. This includes photographs and copies of many Expressionist paintings that are held in private or museum collections, as well as catalogs from Modern Art exhibitions from all over the world. Of particular note are Dr. Gordon's provenance files for all identifiable paintings by Ernst Kirchner. Also included are files pertaining to the various courses taught by Dr. Gordon at the University of Pittsburgh and his professional correspondence.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: This collection was processed by Rebecca Kerman in 2017 and Cassidee Knott in 2018.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Donald Gordon Papers, 1900-1988, UA.90.F46, University Archives, Archives & Special Collections, University of Pittsburgh Library System

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content Notes
scopecontent.p: In 1968 Dr. Gordon published a catalogue raisonné of the paintings of German Expressionist artist Ernst Ludwig Kirchner. This series includes files of provenance research for most of Kirchner's paintings, as well as correspondence with art museums and dealers throughout the United States and Europe pertaining to various Kirchner works. Additionally, there are photocopies of Kirchner's diaries and correspondence which were used by Dr. Gordon while researching the book.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content Notes
scopecontent.p: This subseries contains the provenance files created by Dr. Gordon while reseachering the paintings of Ernst Kirchner. The majority of the files include a form created by Dr. Gordon which he or a correspondent would complete about an individual painting, listing the work's current and previous owners and exhibits, among other information. Some files also contain a photograph of the painting and correspondence.

scopecontent.p: This section contains Dr. Gordon's correspondence with art collectors, museums, and other individuals and institutions in the United States and Europe pertaining to his pursuit of information regarding the dating and provenance of the paintings of Ernst Kirchner. scopecontent.head: Scope and Content Notes
scopecontent.p: This series contains copies and photographs of art exhibit catalogs obtained by Donald Gordon for his 1974 book Modern Art Exhibitions, 1900-1916. In addition to catalogs referenced in his book, this series also contains some catalogs he decided not to include in the final published work.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content Notes
scopecontent.p: Published posthumously in 1987, Expressionism: Art and Idea is a survey of Expressionist painting from its origins in the early 1900s up through the 1970s. This series contains Dr. Gordon's painting inventories from various countries and periods of Expressionism, as well as images used in his book.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content Notes
scopecontent.p: This inventory of artists was created by Dr. Gordon while researching his book on Expressionism. The inventory is arranged chronologically and geographically.
